JS_Markdown.description:
Dynamic Markdown processor based on [link:https://code.google.com/p/pagedown/wiki/PageDown|pagedown] to create HTML in browser.

This module uses parts of code based on pagedown - a [wiki:http://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript|JavaScript] [wiki:http://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown|Markdown] implementation used by [link:http://stackoverflow.com/|Stack Overflow].
The Markdown converter **HAS NOT** been implemented, but extended and integrated by [link:http:/ceusmedia.de/|Ceus Media].
So, this is a modified version of parts of [link:https://code.google.com/p/pagedown/wiki/PageDown|pagedown].

This module will be extended in future to support [link:https://code.google.com/p/pagedown/source/browse/Markdown.Editor.js|Markdown.Editor], which is already a feature of pagedown (prospected to be in version 0.4).

To apply do something like this:
code:js>
var markdownCode        = "MyMarkdownCode";
var markdownConverter   = new Markdown.Converter();
$("#myMarkdownContainer").html(markdownConverter.makeHtml(markdownCode));
<code
Of course you can bind events using jQuery on changing input contents like this:
code:js>
$("#myMarkdownInput").on( "change", function(){
	var markdown    = $(this).val();
	var converter   = new Markdown.Converter();
	$("#myMarkdownView").html(converter.makeHtml(markdown));
});
<code

Server_Log_Exception.description:
Extends server by system log.

Sends mail to developer with exception trace if a developer mail address is defined.
This module can extend normal or server applications but will need an installed application base with mail support.

**Features:**
list>
- stores exceptions into log file (serialized)
- can send mails to one or more mail receivers
<list

**Invokation:**
code>
...
catch( Exception $e ){
	$this->env->getCaptain()->callHook( 'Env', 'logException', $this, array( 'exception' => $e ) );
}
...
<code

If you are sure, that this module is installed, you can use:
code>
...
catch( Exception $e ){
	$this->env->logic->logException->log( $e );

	/* or using logic instance */
	Logic_Log_Exception::getInstance( $this->env )->log( $e );

	/* or using controller */
	Controller_Server_Log_Exception::logException( $e );
}
...
<code
Of course, this method is not the best way, since you bind your code to this module.
Please think about using the hook instead.

UI_JS_Messenger.description:
JavaScript binding to the Hydrogen UI Messenger, which displays result messages after interaction.
Now you can create messages while working with JavaScript. There a 4 methods callable:
code:js>
UI.Messenger.noteSuccess("Work done! What's next, pal?");
UI.Messenger.noteNotice("Maybe you should know that ...");
UI.Messenger.noteError("There was a problem with ...");
UI.Messenger.noteFailure("Ouh crap! There was an unexpected error with ...");
<code
These methods rely on <cite>UI.Messenger.renderMessage()</cite> with a second parameter, for example:
code:js>
UI.Messenger.renderMessage("This is a test","notice");
<code
This second parameter can be one of {success,notice,error,failure}.
